definitions.definition: a part of the trunk or a large branch of a tree that has fallen or been cut off.
examples: branch, trunk; Morepiece of wood; timber, firewood "a fallen log"Morepiece of wood; timber, firewood a fallen log

definitions.definition: an official record of events during the voyage of a ship or aircraft.
synonyms: tally; trademarkdaytimer "a log of phone calls"

definitions.definition: a regular or systematic record of incidents or observations.
examples: keep a detailed log of your activities
synonyms: tally; trademarkdaytimer "a log of phone calls"

definitions.definition: an apparatus for determining the speed of a ship, originally consisting of a float attached to a knotted line wound on a reel, the distance run out in a certain time being used as an estimate of the vessel's speed.
